ly and effectively coordinate and manage field trials at customer sites. The Director of Bioprocess Applications Engineering position will serve as an advisor to the product development team regarding projects, tasks, and daily operations to meet deadlines or resolve complex problems. Assignments will be task and project oriented, and problems are complex and have a diverse scope. Candidate will be responsible for recommending modifications to operating schedules, performance requirements, budgets, and schedules. Candidate must have the ability to manage and build team members and direct reports. Requirements Minimum of a BS/MS or PhD in chemical engineering, pharmaceutical sciences, life science or chemistry or biochemistry with 5-10+ years of experience. pharmaceutical process development or technology implementation. Excellent hands-on laboratory skills. Ability to independently design, plan and schedule experiments and carry out data analysis. Ability to develop test protocols and present reports to customers and derive relevant conclusions and/or recommendations for future courses of action. Ability to apply high-level problem-solving skills. Well-developed verbal and written communication skills and ability to respond to and prioritize customer and internal team needs. Ability to produce high quality written trial reports and other appropriate documentation and content that appropriately captures results of trial work. Able to collect, organize, and analyze data resulting in conclusions/recommendations. Maintain attention to details and demonstrate good communication skills. Ability to manage and mentor a 4+ person process development/applications team. Job Type: Full-time Pay: $115,000.00 - $144,000.00 per year Benefits: 401(k) 401(k) Matching Health Insurance Paid Time Off Parental Leave Relocation Assistance Schedule: Monday to Friday Experience: bioprocess: 5 years (Required) Education: Bachelor's (Required) Location: South San Francisco, CA 94080 (Required) Company's website: teraporetech.com Benefit Conditions: Only full-time employees eligible Work Remotely: No ",
